# data/ directory — SQLite queue database lives here

This directory holds runtime state that must NOT be committed to git.

- `queue.db`           — live SQLite database (gitignored)
- `queue.db-wal`       — WAL journal (gitignored, managed by SQLite)
- `queue.db-shm`       — shared memory file (gitignored, managed by SQLite)
- `queue.db.example`   — empty schema snapshot committed for documentation

## GHA artifact strategy

At the end of every workflow job that touches the queue, upload the DB:

```yaml
- uses: actions/upload-artifact@v4
  with:
    name: queue-db
    path: data/queue.db
    retention-days: 7
    overwrite: true
```

At the start of every job, download it:

```yaml
- uses: actions/download-artifact@v4
  with:
    name: queue-db
    path: data/
  continue-on-error: true   # first run: no artifact yet, migration will create it
```

Then run the (idempotent) migration:

```yaml
- run: npx tsx src/services/queue/migrate.ts
```
